rComments: - Get ready to use your printer because there is a lot of printing that needs to be done - Does a lot of subtle flexing - Will be very critical with your paper if she reads it, but very helpful - Very good at helping students understand concepts - Very knowledgeable - If she was a Shakespearean character, hubris would be her greatest weakness
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'So many papers', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Best philosophy teacher at UofT! Professor Wilson took so much time to help me get out of my shell. I have had every other Philosophy instructor at the St. George campus make me feel like I was an idiot. Not only did she help boost my confidence, she made me realize that I really have an aptitude for metaphysics.

This course is an absolute must if you have the desire to become a better writer. You really have to earn your grade, but the feedback she gives will help you understand the areas in which you can improve. You will really acknowledge her influence when you find yourself doing better in subsequent courses.

She is just wonderful. She spends a lot of time in giving good feedback on papers and assignments. She will challenge your thoughts and will make you think outside of the box. She is not an easy marker, but this does not mean that you cannot get a good mark in her class. If you work hard and if you're dedicated enough, you will receive a great mark

Jessica is probably the best professor I've ever had. She REALLY wants you to take this course in order to LEARN. She will help you in any way that she can. She is extremely funny and is a downright amazing human being. You do have to work for your mark, but she allows for bonus marks if you make a legit attempt to improve your writing skills.

The best philosophy professor I have had to date. She is extremely clear, and you feel like you're actually learning something. Very intelligent and competent. The professor always makes the difference, and I believe any course taught by her would be rewarding.

Teaching wise ok. Getting your work graded, takes a long time. Final assignment was due april 12, today may 3rd still not marked. Not sure if a UTSC thing but all my courses at UTSG came within 5 days of the final papers. Couldn't apply for an internship because I still havent received my final mark. They needed all marks to be noted on transcript.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Lots of homework', 'Participation matters']

rComments: shes a babysitting prof. u have to strictly follow her outlines or suffer a bad mark. go to st george and study under margaret morrison or imogen dic-kie. they treat you like adults and respect your philosophical abilities.

She's my FAV philosophy prof! Super sweet and funny. There's a lot of work in PHLB99 like weekly essay draftsoutlines and the final essay, but it genuinely makes you a better writer. Definitely take her class if you're in philosophy; you won't regret it. Just go with an open mind and put your hand up every once in a while and you'll be just fine.
teacherRatingTags: ['Participation matters', 'Get ready to read', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: she is not only a teacher, she is a mentor as well- she is there when you need her during her office hours - although she might seem intimidating at first, she is a great person and has a big heart - i learnt a lot from her and looking forward to taking more classes with her! TAKE A CLASS WITH HER only if you want to learn and eager for education

Best professor I have ever had. Extremely approachable and gives great feedback and comments. Learned so much in her Writing Philosophy class, improved my essays in all my classes by at least 10%. Definitely a great prof!

Professor Wilson may initially seem intimidating however do not be fooled by your initial perceptions ... She is extremely nice, very smart, and very helpful! I learnt a lot during the course and regret not taking philosophy courses with her earlier! Would def. recommend taking a course with her!!

Jess is one of the most talented philosophers I have ever had the opportunity to study with. She is thoroughly dedicated to her students, offers tremendously helpful comments on every assignment, and is engaging in the classroom. She has made me a better writer, and a better philosopher. She is an invaluable asset to any student on the UTSC campus.

Taking Metaphysics with Wilson inspired me to major in philosophy. She routinely goes beyond course content, teaching how to analyze, summarize, and critique readings with rigor and precision. Her thorough marking and criticism has made me a better philosopher and writer. She's an invaluable support for students pursuing philosophy professionally.

Very good professor! Actually, one of the best professors I've had, if she isn't the best professor I've had. I've taken several of her classes, including: PHLB60, PHLB99, and PHLC60, will continue to take more of her classes in the future. She is super duper smart, and the comments she leaves on your papers are very helpful. 10/10.

Jess is super cool and really knows her stuff.  She is young and can relate to her students and their issues with the class.  Her class is easy if you give the speeches and she is charasmatic so it's easy to make yourself go to class.  I definately recommend her for the speech requirement.
